{
  "text": "It is likely that the arms serve as a counterweight to shift the body COM away from the direction of the fall [CITATION_1] or generate restoring torque to reduce angular momentum of the body [CITATION_2] . Therefore, it is likely that the contribution of arm movements in children may be even greater during reactive balance tasks. Future research should examine upper limb dynamics in the recovery phase of a perturbation during standing and locomotion.",
